  "prompt": "What are some locations in Tennessee that are suitable for a prom?",
  "response": "Tennessee offers a range of beautiful and unique venues that are suitable for hosting a prom. Here are several options across the state:\n\n1. **The Bell Tower - Nashville**: This restored historic church features a modern design and offers a large event space right in downtown Nashville. It\u2019s perfect for a sophisticated prom night.\n\n2. **The Peabody Hotel - Memphis**: Known for its charm and elegance, The Peabody offers grand ballrooms that provide a luxurious setting for a prom.\n\n3. **Hunter Museum of American Art - Chattanooga**: Overlooking the Tennessee River, this museum offers a stunning backdrop for any event and a large space for dancing and celebration.\n\n4. **Knoxville Botanical Garden - Knoxville**: For those seeking an outdoor venue, the lush gardens provide a romantic and picturesque setting for a prom.\n\n5. **The Emporium Center - Knoxville**: Located in downtown Knoxville, this historic building offers a spacious gallery that can be transformed into a beautiful dance floor.\n\n6. **Discovery Park of America - Union City**: This venue combines a unique setting with interactive exhibits that could make for a memorable prom experience.\n\n7. **The Barn at Sycamore Farms - Arrington**: Just south of Nashville, this venue offers a rustic and elegant barn setting with beautiful grounds and a scenic lake.\n\n8. **Cheekwood Estate & Gardens - Nashville**: With beautiful gardens and a historic mansion, Cheekwood provides a stunning and elegant backdrop for a prom.\n\n9. **The Carnegie Hotel - Johnson City**: This hotel offers a classic and sophisticated environment with beautiful ballrooms perfect for a formal event.\n\n10. **The Old Woolen Mill - Cleveland**: This historic venue provides a unique and rustic atmosphere, ideal for a prom with a vintage or industrial theme.\n\nWhen choosing a venue, consider factors like the size of your group, the theme of the prom, and any additional amenities or services the location may offer.",
